  <h2 id="introduction">Introduction</h2>
  <p>
    The story of digital image formats is a fascinating journey through nearly five decades of
    innovation, competition, patent disputes, and evolving technology. From the earliest bitmap
    files that stored every single pixel individually to modern AI-enhanced compression algorithms
    that can reconstruct images from remarkably little data, image formats have continuously
    evolved to meet the demands of new hardware, new use cases, and an ever-growing volume of
    digital imagery. Understanding this history helps explain why we have so many image formats
    today and where the technology is heading next.
  </p>

